    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-03-09T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-03-09T06:00:00-05:00" n="371"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d371">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.76/91: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-03-09T19:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 9, 1938—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 9—12:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>370. Reference my 347, March 2, 7 p.m. Japanese Consulate General has now replied
                    to radio companies that it is unable to accept their proposals, adding that
                    while obstacles continue to exist to use of the Chinese Government Radio
                    Administration equipment in the French concession they are doing their utmost to
                    restore radio communications and feel confident that the Shanghai station under
                    Japanese control will succeed in rendering satisfactory service at no distant
                    date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
